section.def:
ASTM,
            in relation to a test method, means the test method published by ASTM
            International;

colourant
                (色劑) means a solution of dyes or a suspension of
            pigments;

diluent
                (稀釋液) means a liquid such as an organic solvent,
            thinner or water which when added to a regulated product reduces its viscosity;

paragraph.content:
a regulated consumer product listed in section 1 of Part 2 of Schedule
                        3, means an exempt compound within the meaning of section 2 of
                        Part 2 of Schedule 3;

a regulated consumer product listed in Parts 3, 4 and 5 of Schedule
                        3, means an exempt compound within the meaning of Part 6 of
                        Schedule 3;

section.def:
manufacturer
                (生產商) means a person who manufactures in Hong
            Kong a regulated product;

NIOSH
            means the National Institute for Occupational Safety and Health of the United
            States;

paragraph.content:
a regulated consumer product, means the maximum limit of the volatile
                    organic compound content specified for that regulated consumer product in
                        Part 2, 3 or 4 of Schedule 3 (as may be applicable);

that is intended to be used in lithographic printing, namely, a
                    planographic printing process in which the image and non-image areas are on the
                    same plane and are chemically differentiated;

section.def:
US
                EPA
            means the United States Environmental Protection Agency;

paragraph.content:
when dilution of the paint with solvent or thinner is necessary before
                    application, the brand and full name of the diluent to be used and its specific
                    gravity;

the type of regulated vessel paint or regulated pleasure craft paint to
                    which the regulated vessel paint or regulated pleasure craft paint
                    belongs;

the volatile organic compound content of the regulated fountain solution or
                    regulated printing machine cleaning agent in a ready to use condition;
                    and

immersion in water, waste water, or chemical solutions (aqueous and
                            non-aqueous solutions) or chronic exposure of interior surfaces to
                            moisture condensation;

acute or chronic exposure to corrosive, caustic or acidic agents,
                            or similar chemicals, chemical fumes, chemical mixtures or
                            solutions;

repeated heavy abrasion, including mechanical wear and repeated
                            scrubbing with industrial solvents, cleaners or scouring agents;
                            or

are capable of being applied directly from the container by brush
                            or roller under normal conditions (the normal conditions being ambient
                            temperatures between 16°C and 27°C);

section.def:
varnishes
                        (光油) means clear wood finishes that are
                    formulated with various resins to dry by chemical reaction;

td.p:
represents the weight of volatile organic compounds in grams
                                        of any colourant added to tint base per litre of material,
                                        as provided by the paint manufacturer or importer;

represents the weight of volatile organic compounds in grams
                                        of any colourant added to tint base per litre of material,
                                        as provided by the paint manufacturer or importer;

section.def:
insect repellent (驅蟲劑) means any pesticide product that is
                    designed to be applied on human skin, hair or attire worn on humans in order to
                    prevent contact with or repel biting insects or arthropods;

paragraph.content:
in calculating the volatile organic compound content of the regulated
                        consumer product, fragrances incorporated into the product up to a combined
                        level of 2% by weight of the product shall be excluded;

in calculating the volatile organic compound content of the regulated
                    consumer product, fragrances incorporated into the product up to a combined
                    level of 2% by weight of the product shall be excluded;

